<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Fiona Falkiner is undergoing IVF to have a baby with her fiancée Hayley Willis, and she's been documenting the journey for her fans. </p>

<p>And the 37-year-old recently suffered what she thought was a devastating set back, when she thought she'd taken her hormonal medication at the wrong time. </p>

<p>She said on her What The IVF podcast this week: 'I just cried all night long. I was filled with complete fear and dread and thought I had put everything in jeopardy after all we had been through. I have never beaten myself up so much'. </p>

<p>Long road: Fiona Falkiner (right) is undergoing IVF to have a baby with her fiancée Hayley Willis (left), and she's been documenting the journey for her fans</p>

<p>Luckily, the former Biggest Loser host quickly learned she'd taken the medicine at the right time. </p>

<p>Fiona also says she had a 'good feeling' about her latest harvest of eggs, after a psychic told her she'd have two children - perhaps even twins. </p>

<p>'I'm feeling really good this time. My mindset is much more positive than the last round. I think having two embryos rather than one helps; having a back-up lessens the pressure,' she said. </p>

<p>Upset: And the 37-year-old recently suffered what she thought was a devastating set back, when she thought she'd taken her hormonal medication at the wrong time. 'I just cried all night long. I have never beaten myself up so much' she said om her podcast </p>

<p>Fiona recently revealed her 'traumatic' and 'lonely' journey in an interview with The Daily Telegraph. </p>

<p>She told the paper: 'It is you and your body against all odds. Women don't really talk about it until after the fact. It can be really quite traumatic.'  </p>

<p>In the same interview, Hayley, 30, revealed that she, too, hopes to carry a baby, shortly after Fiona gives birth. </p>

<p>Hayley said: 'Fi is going first because she is older. I really want to carry a bub too but Fi will go first just because of the body clock on fertility, so her going first is best.'</p>

<p> Ready to be mums: Fiona also says she had a 'good feeling' about her latest harvest of eggs, after a psychic told her she'd have two children - perhaps even twins</p>

<p> Coming soon: Hayley, 30, revealed that she, too, hopes to carry a baby, shortly after Fiona gives birth</p>

<p>Fiona and Hayley announced their engagement in April 2019, after 10 months of dating each other. The couple have already purchased a house together. </p>

<p>The romantic proposal took place at sunset on a private beach at The Moso resort in Vanuatu, with Hayley presenting her partner with a diamond ring.  </p>

<p>The two women will tie the knot later this year in an intimate wedding ceremony.   </p>

<p>The couple haven't announced a wedding date yet, but they've previously stated that it will be a 'low-key' ceremony with friends and family.</p>

